# Per-clone overlay configuration. Copy this file to `local.properties` and edit to taste.
# `local.properties` is git-ignored; `local.properties.example` is committed and provides the
# defaults used when no `local.properties` exists.
#
# androidx.sources: comma-separated Gradle project paths to build from the upstream androidx
# checkout. The relative directory under `androidx/` is derived by replacing `:` with `/`,
# unless an entry uses the `:path = relative/dir` form to override.
#
# Stubs for every other project referenced by these are auto-populated.
#
# androidx.recursiveProjectDiscovery controls which nested projects are auto-included when an
# entry points at a parent directory. Explicit androidx.sources entries are always included.
# Values: main, samples, tests, benchmarks, all, none. Combine with commas, e.g. main,samples.
# Default is main, which avoids accidentally configuring nested sample/test/benchmark projects.

# Default config: the RemoteCompose trees. `samples` is included because the @Preview functions
# that compose-preview renders live in the `*-samples` modules. The convention plugin
# (androidchka.extras.gradle.kts) applies ee.schimke.composeai.preview to every Android *source*
# module — i.e. whatever you list here — so changing androidx.sources changes which modules get
# previews; there's no hardcoded module list.
androidx.sources=:compose:remote,:wear:compose:remote
androidx.recursiveProjectDiscovery=main,samples

# Extra Gradle config (additional plugins, dependencies, task tweaks) is applied via the
# convention plugin at build-logic/src/main/kotlin/androidchka.extras.gradle.kts. Edit that
# file directly — it's a normal Kotlin DSL build script.
